{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Barnett Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Barnett Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Victoria Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|70|59|S|167|30|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Smith Inlet (Victoria Land)|Smith Inlet]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Barnett Glacier''' ({{Coord|70|59|S|167|30|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a large [[glacier]] in the [[Anare Mountains]] that flows east along the south side of [[Tapsell Foreland]] into [[Smith Inlet (Victoria Land)|Smith Inlet]], northern [[Victoria Land]], [[Antarctica]]. It was mapped by the [[United States Geological Survey]] (USGS) from surveys and from [[U.S. Navy]] air photos, 1960–63, and named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] after [[Donald C. Barnett]], USGS topographic engineer, a member of [[USGS Topo East and West]], 1962–63, in which the expedition extended geodetic control from the area of [[Cape Hallett]] to the [[Wilson Hills]]<!-- sic --> (Topo West) and from the foot of [[Beardmore Glacier]] through the [[Horlick Mountains]] (Topo East). The glacier lies on the [[Pennell Coast]], a portion of Antarctica lying between [[Cape Williams]] and [[Cape Adare]].
