{{Infobox film | name = Black Sky: The Race for Space | image = Black_Sky,_The_Race_For_Space,_dvd_cover.jpeg | caption = | director = | producer = | starring = [[Burt Rutan]], [[Paul Allen]], [[James Benson]] | music = | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = Discovery Communications | released = 2005 | runtime = 143 | country = USA | language = English | budget = | gross = }} '''''Black Sky: The Race For Space''''' is a 2005 [[Discovery Channel]] documentary about [[Space Ship One]], and how a small team backed by [[Paul Allen]] achieved human suborbital spaceflight and won the [[Ansari X Prize]]. It contains insights about how the rocketplane was built, the challenges they faced when they flew it, the vision of [[Burt Rutan]] about the future of this technology (tier two and three), and his thoughts about NASA and government.<ref>{{cite web |title=Review - Black Sky: The Race For Space and Winning The X-Prize DVDs|url= http://www.collectspace.com/resources/reviews/dvd/black_sky.html|publisher= collectspace|date= }}</ref> It won a [[Peabody Award]] in 2004.<ref>[http://www.peabodyawards.com/award-profile/black-sky-the-race-for-space 64th Annual Peabody Awards], May 2005.</ref>
